The paper discusses the intersection of two areas of research: lifted probabilistic inference and symbolic dynamic programming for lifted stochastic planning. These areas are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), programming languages (cs.PL), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
